parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The ABS warning light comes on
the brakes fail to engage or engage partially
the rear wheel locks up
the vehicle pulls to one side
the brakes feel soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The rear brake seizes or locks up
the rear brake does not release
the vehicle stops abruptly
the rear brake makes a squealing noise
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes fail to engage or engage partially
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brake fluid level is low
the brake warning light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks in the plastic fuel pump assembly can cause fuel leaks, leading to a fire hazard, especially when the assembly is located near the hot engine.
symptoms: Fuel smell
fuel mist
cracks in the fuel pump assembly
specifically where the female side of the quick disconnect screws into the pump assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning idle control valve can cause the engine to idle erratically, leading to a loss of throttle response, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Idle jumps to high RPM
erratic idle
sticking idle valve plunger
lack of throttle response
stalling
sudden drops in RPM.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective airbox can cause the throttle to stick, leading to unintended acceleration, loss of engine braking, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Throttle sticking
loss of engine braking
unintended acceleration
high idle
erratic idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive can cause oil to leak onto the rear tire, leading to loss of control and potentially causing accidents or fatalities.
symptoms: Oil leaking from the final drive
oil on the rear tire
bearing failure
gear oil leakage
sudden loss of traction or control
especially in corners.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause the fuel gauge to provide inaccurate readings, leading to unexpected fuel exhaustion, engine stalling, and potentially, accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel gauge shows incorrect fuel levels
sudden loss of power or stalling
no warning issued by the vehicle to the rider
fuel cap comes open while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gas cap can cause fuel to spill or leak while driving, leading to accidents, injuries, or fires.
symptoms: Gas cap comes open while driving
fuel spills or leaks
rider experiences burns or other injuries.
